#   BRO-003: BRO-002 status-row regressions — sub-relay rows + patch codes

[BRO-002] (landed `25abfece`+`acbda302`) converged every verb onto ONE
per-(sub)module table hunk rendered by the single `HUNKu8sFeedBanner` path.
That land regressed status-row output in two cases that four previously-green
tests assert.  Both are rendering/relay gaps, not logic gaps — the verbs do
the work (counters and prose lines are correct), but the per-file/per-status
ROW no longer surfaces in the report a consumer parses.

##  Failing tests (all green before BRO-002; SUBS-004/005 repros landed 2026-06-06)
 -  `#355 be-put-09-sub-only-dirty-exit` — bare `be put` with only a mounted
    sub dirty: direct (non-tlv) stdout shows only the module header `vendor/sub`
    but NOT the path-prefixed per-file row `put\tvendor/sub/core.c` the test
    greps for (`test/put/09-sub-only-dirty-exit/run.sh:44`).
 -  `#354 be-put-08-sub-stage-all-both-dirty` — same family (parent + sub both
    dirty; sub's row missing from the report).
 -  `#194 be-delete-07-sub-delete-all-missing` — same family on the delete verb.
 -  `#78 SNIFFpatch` — `FAIL: expected 'modl' status row in report`: the
    modify/delete-kept-ours case prints the prose line ("modify/delete on d.c —
    kept ours") and bumps `mod-del-kept=1`, but emits no per-row status code
    `modl` in the table.

##  Input

### Context
 -  BRO-002 emits ONE per-(sub)module table hunk; mutators stream rows to
    stderr in direct-tty mode, and flush the batched table hunk only in
    `--tlv`/relay mode (BRO-002 "RULED — channels").
 -  Sub recursion forks a `--tlv` child, captures its hunk stream, and replays
    it path-prefixed via `HUNKu8sRelay` (`dog/HUNK.c`).  The per-file rows live
    INSIDE that relayed table hunk's `(text,toks)` body.
 -  In the failing put/delete cases the report is captured to a FILE (not a
    tty) without `--tlv`, so neither the tty-stream path nor the tlv-flush path
    emits the sub's per-file rows — only the module header survives.
 -  Shared row builder is `dog/ROWS.{c,h}` (BRO-002); patch status codes are
    emitted by `sniff/PATCH.c` through it (the `modl`/`conf`/`take` codes).

### Goals
 -  `be put` / `be delete` / `be patch` to a plain pipe (non-tty, non-tlv) emit
    the per-file/per-status ROWS again — including rows from a RELAYED sub
    table hunk, path-prefixed — restoring the `<date>\t<verb>\t<path>` (and
    `patch\t<code>\t<path>`) grammar the tests parse.
 -  `SNIFFpatch`: the modify/delete-kept case emits a `modl` status row, not
    just a counter + prose line.

### Constraints
 -  Keep [Verb channels]: don't regress the tty streaming or the `--tlv` batch.
    The gap is specifically the direct-to-pipe (non-tty, non-tlv) rendering of
    a relayed sub table hunk and of the patch `modl` code.
 -  Renderer/relay rework stays in `dog/HUNK.c`+`dog/ROWS.c`+`sniff/PATCH.c`;
    producers only produce hunks (presentation is bro's job).
 -  `abc/` untouched.

##  WIP

### Likely cause (to confirm)
 -  The relayed sub table hunk's body rows are dropped (or only its banner
    header rendered) when the parent re-emits in a non-tlv, non-tty mode —
    `HUNKu8sRelay` / `HUNKu8sFeedBanner` direct-mode path likely renders the
    header band but elides the `(text,toks)` rows.  And `sniff/PATCH.c` never
    appends a `modl` row for `mod-del-kept` (only increments the counter).

